ENTRY            F1164   20260115   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F1164001   20260115   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  9         20
TITLE      The anomalous inelastic scattering of alpha particles
AUTHOR     (M.Crut,D.R.Sweetman,N.S.Wall)
INSTITUTE  (1USAMIT)
REFERENCE  (J,NP,17,655,1960)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,1USAMIT)
DETECTOR   (SCIN,CSICR,PROPC) The basic detector was CsI(Tl)
           scintillation spectrometer preceded by a thin gas
           counter. This counter assembly was mounted external
           to a 10.2 cm diameter scattering chamber. The gas
           counter was about 1 cm in front of the scintillation
           crystal. The total thickness of this proportional
           counter including gas and windows was equivalent to
           approximately 5 cm of air.
METHOD     (EDE,PHD,EXTB)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) Relative error
           (ERR-2,,15.) The background subtraction should not
           introduce an error of greater than + - 15%
HISTORY    (20120327C)
           (20260115A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           DATA-ERR -> ERR-1.
ENDBIB              20
COMMON               3          3
EN         E-LVL-ERR  ERR-1
MEV        MEV        PER-CENT
        30.        0.3        10.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           27
